ElementDescription: [This final section will be to anyone who has drank since one month before they became pregnant and did not drink everyday.] Each page will ask about each day in four week sets and present you with two calendars for reference. Please only mark days that would be different that the typical week you marked above. For example, if you quit drinking for a month, please mark each day in that month you quit as 0. Or, if you drank more on a Friday, indicate that. People find it helpful to think about paydays, birthdays, celebrations, hospitalizations, arrest, or other events that may increase their drinking.
Have you had any alcohol since one month before you were pregnant?
Notes: 0 = No, not even a sip. [Participants will not be shown the rest of the TLFB]; 1 = I drank one month before I was pregnant, but stopped once I found out I was pregnant.; 2 = Yes, I have drank since one month before my pregnancy.;

ElementDescription: [Those answer b to #1] How often did you drink one month before your pregnancy before you stopped drinking?
Notes: 0 = Everyday [Participant will answer the number of drinks they have in a typical week, but will not be shown the day-to-day calendar]; 1 = 5-6 days per week; 2 = 3-4 days per week; 3 = 2 days per week; 4 = 1 day a week; 5 = On special occasions (such as your birthday and holidays);

ElementDescription: [Those who answer c to #1] How often have you drank since one month before you were pregnant?
Notes: 0 = Everyday [Participant will answer the number of drinks they have in a typical week, but will not be shown the day-to-day calendar.]; 1 = 5-6 days per week; 2 = 3-4 days per week; 3 = 2 days per week; 4 = 1 day a week; 5 = On special occasions (such as your birthday and holidays); 6 = Never, not even on sip. ;
